{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1d1eb4c3-f25c-4fec-b01a-e1b2f2bbd996","content":"Here's how to set up **NuGet Trusted Publishing** using OIDC — no API keys needed.\n\n## Step 1: Configure NuGet.org\n\n1. Go to **nuget.org → Manage Packages → your package → Trusted Publishers**\n   (or set it up when first pushing via the API key one last time)\n2. Add a **GitHub** trusted publisher:\n   - **Repository owner:** `myorg`\n   - **Repository name:** `mylib`\n   - **Workflow:** `publish.yml`\n   - **Environment:** `nuget.org`\n\n## Step 2: Create a GitHub Environment\n\nIn your repo: **Settings → Environments → New environment** → name it `nuget.org`. Optionally add protection rules (e.g., required reviewers).\n\n## Step 3: Add the workflow","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_nJJcQAg5wzkhhkJcfLBb3M","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Creating NuGet publish workflow"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_AmzWJweuRJFuqDtATTgfWj","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"mkdir -p /tmp/sv-89c3ff62a85b4fcc8810b43d48467391/.github/workflows","description":"Create workflows directory"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"Create workflows directory"}],"interactionId":"05c4c29c-b08b-413e-bf66-b2587019a814","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to set up secure NuGet publishing from GitHub Actions using trusted publishing (no API keys). This is a knowledge/guidance question, not a code task. Let me provide a concise answer.\n\nNuGet.org now supports trusted publishing via OIDC (OpenID Connect), similar to PyPI. This lets GitHub Actions authenticate without storing API keys as secrets.\n\nLet me outline the steps:\n\n1. Configure NuGet.org to trust the GitHub repo\n2. Set up a GitHub Actions workflow\n\nActually, let me check — NuGet.org's trusted publishers feature. As of my knowledge, NuGet.org does support this. \n\nNow I need to walk through the actual setup process. On NuGet.org, you link your package to a GitHub repository as a trusted publisher, then in the workflow I'll show how to use the OIDC token for authentication instead of API keys.","outputTokens":548},"id":"7196fae9-3238-48fb-ae0a-8f1b98d5b072","timestamp":"2026-04-08T00:45:06.601Z","parentId":"0594f3be-53e0-452c-b0fb-19c1eb07d178"}
